                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1907">Sāhdē Ḥmīrāyē</persName> is commemorated in
            <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/254">The Himyarite Martyrs (text)</title>, a work
          surviving in at least 11 manuscripts including <bibl type="MSS" xml:id="witness1">variantes du ms
            Berlin, Königliche Bibliothek, syr. 75 (Sachau 222), f. 455-464</bibl>. It commemorates
          the martrydom of Christians of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/474">Ḥimyar</placeName> who were killed in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/464">Nagran</placeName> in the sixth century by the Jewish king Yusuf. </note>
